  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 47a621783cb453147b01764dde5ed130, type: 3}
  m_Name: R1_4_WriteRecipe
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  dialogueLines:
  - There is one more thing you must understand before brewing properly.
  - Not every important step involves adding an ingredient.
  - Most recipes require the mixture to be stirred a specific number of times.
  - Stirring helps the magical properties blend together correctly.
  - Without it, a potion may become unstable... or fail entirely.
  - In this first recipe, stirring once is enough. But do so very carefully.
  - Now we have everything we need for the recipe.
  - You can use the enchanted table in this workshop to write everything down.
  - Remember the order carefully, dear.
  - First, light the fire.
  - Then add a Strawberry.
  - The last ingredient is 2 Bat wings.
  - And finally, stir carefully.
  - Well done!
  - Recipes are more than ingredients. They are instructions arranged with purpose.
  - When the sequence is correct, the magic flows naturally through the brew.
  - You've taken your first step as a Moonwarden.
